description.narrative: UNICEF provided technical and financial support to MoH for sugar-sweetened beverage tax evaluation; supported MoH on food fortification programme, World Breastfeeding Week and the extension ofthelandscape analysis. An SBCC creative plan to reduce sugary drinks is expected to roll out in 2022. Two reports were published: Nutrition Landscape Analysis (Volume I) and Digital Marketing of Unhealthy Food and Drink to Children Across the Region. A series of polls on eating habits among young people during the pandemic was conducted. Initial product scoping was completed as part of the Southeast Asia Consortium for Complementary Feeding (COMMIT) desk review process. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:03/02/2022
